@node cfservd HostnameKeys, cfservd IfElapsed, DenyConnectionsFrom, cfservd control
@subsection HostnameKeys in cfservd

If this variable is set to true/on, it causes cfservd to
lookup and store trusted public keys according to their
DNS fully qualified host name, instead of using the IP address.
This can be useful in environments where hosts do not have fixed
IP addresses, but do have fixed hostnames.

@smallexample

  HostnameKeys = ( on )

@end smallexample
This method of storing keys is not recommended for sites with
fixed IP addresses, since it removes one security barrier
from a potential attacker by potentially allowing DNS spoofing.

