@node LogAllConnections, LogEncryptedTransfers, cfservd IfElapsed, cfservd control
@subsection LogAllConnections

If set to true, every successful connection will be logged to syslog.
This could be useful for identifying abuses of the service, if the server
should come under attack, e.g. a denial of service attack. The IP address
can then be excluded from the allowed connections list.

@c ...........................................
@c SUBSECTION
@c ...........................................

@node LogEncryptedTransfers, MaxConnections, LogAllConnections, cfservd control
@subsection LogEncryptedTransfers

If set to true, every successful request for a file that is granted
access only with an encrypted connection is logged in syslog.

